  • Method Details

    • create

      public static void create(Apartment apartment, Long buildingId) throws BuildingNotFoundException
      Creates a new apartment and associates it with an existing building. This method opens a new Hibernate session and transaction. If the building with the provided ID does not exist, it throws a BuildingNotFoundException.
      Parameters:
      apartment - The Apartment object to be created and persisted.
      buildingId - The ID of the Building to which the apartment will be associated.
      Throws:
      BuildingNotFoundException - If a building with the specified ID does not exist in the database.

    • getById

      public static Apartment getById(long id) throws ApartmentNotFoundException
      Retrieves an apartment by its ID.
      Parameters:
      id - The ID of the apartment to retrieve.
      Returns:
      The found Apartment object.
      Throws:
      ApartmentNotFoundException - If no apartment is found with the given ID.

    • getApartments

      public static List<Apartment> getApartments()
      Retrieves all apartments in the database.

    • addOwnerToApartment

      public static void addOwnerToApartment(Long ownerId, Long apartmentId) throws ApartmentNotFoundException, OwnerNotFoundException
      Adds an owner to an apartment and updates the bidirectional relationship.
      Parameters:
      ownerId - The ID of the owner to be added to the apartment.
      apartmentId - The ID of the apartment to which the owner is to be added.
      Throws:
      ApartmentNotFoundException - If the apartment with the specified ID does not exist.
      OwnerNotFoundException - If the owner with the specified ID does not exist.

    • addLivingToApartment

      public static void addLivingToApartment(Living living, Long apartmentId) throws ApartmentNotFoundException
      Adds a living entity to an apartment.
      Parameters:
      living - The Living object to be added to the apartment.
      apartmentId - The ID of the apartment to which the living entity is to be added.
      Throws:
      ApartmentNotFoundException - If the apartment with the specified ID does not exist.
